<DOC><DOCNO> AP890525-0092 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-05-25-89 1226EST</FILEID><FIRST>r i AM-BRF--Japan-US     05-25 0146</FIRST><SECOND>AM-BRF--Japan-US,0151</SECOND><HEAD>Japan to Replace its Ambassador to the United States</HEAD><DATELINE>TOKYO (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   The Foreign Ministry has selected Ryohei Murata asthe new ambassador to the United States, replacing Nobuo Matsunaga,officials said Thursday.   Murata, administrative vice foreign minister, is expected toreplace Matsunaga in September, said a ministry official, speakingon condition of anonymity.   Matsunaga became ambassador to the United States in January1985, after serving as deputy foreign minister.   The Asahi Shimbun newspaper reported the decision came becausethe ministry thinks it is a good time for the personnel change nowthat the Bush administration has settled in.   The ministry has also decided to promote Takakazu Kuriyama,deputy vice minister for political affairs, to administrative viceminister in July, according to the Foreign Ministry.   Hisashi Owada, ambassador to the Organization for EconomicCooperation and Development will take Kuriyama's place, theofficial said.</TEXT></DOC>